						               													<description>&amp;ldquo;The Lorn Keep was once a magnificent castle that guarded the entrance to a wealthy valley kingdom. The masters of the keep grew rich collecting taxes from the merchants seeking safe passage into the valley. With time, the kingdom fell and the keep along with it. Now the ruins are a popular destination for adventurers and treasure hunters, many of whom are never seen from again.&amp;rdquo; - Jaden the Elder&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Ruins of the Lorn Keep is an easy-to-learn, quick-to-play dungeon crawl. Play a warrior, a thief or a wizard searching for treasure, powerful magical items, and fame. Each character excels at one of the three different dungeon challenge types. Part dungeon crawl, part memory game, Ruins of the Lorn Keep is highly portable and can be played nearly anywhere.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;During a player's turn, a card is turned face-up and dice rolled to try and beat a monster or win a treasure. Each card is worth victory points. The first player to 10 points wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
